# EF Core (`apps/api/Data`)

## DbContext

`AppDbContext` — `DbSet<User>`, `DbSet<TaskItem>`; configurations applied from assembly.

## Entity configuration

```csharp
// ✅ GOOD — inherit BaseEntityConfiguration<T>
public class TaskItemConfiguration : BaseEntityConfiguration<TaskItem>
{
    public override void Configure(EntityTypeBuilder<TaskItem> builder)
    {
        base.Configure(builder);
        builder.Property(t => t.Title).IsRequired().HasMaxLength(200);
        builder.ToTable("Tasks");
    }
}
```

## Migrations

- Folder: `apps/api/Migrations/`
- Apply on startup: `DbInitializer.InitializeAsync` → `MigrateAsync()`
- **Never** `EnsureCreated()`

## Seeding

`DbInitializer` seeds admin user when `Users` table is empty (`Seed:AdminEmail`, `Seed:AdminPassword`).

## Interceptors

`AuditableEntityInterceptor` sets `CreatedAt` / `UpdatedAt` on `BaseEntity`.

## Provider switch

`Database:Provider` — `Sqlite` | `SqlServer` | `PostgreSQL` (see skill `switch-database-provider`).

```csharp
// ❌ BAD
Database.EnsureCreated();

// ✅ GOOD
await context.Database.MigrateAsync();
```
